Inspection of equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for wells Introduction to Zhengzhou’s equipment for well wall brick modules:
Zhengzhou Yixin is a professional manufacturer of equipment for concrete inspection well modular brick production in China, including machinery for constructing inspection wells and modular walls for well structures. The company offers production lines ranging from semi-automatic to fully automated systems.
Through years of practice and development, we have now established a reputation for producing high-quality equipment, mainly including hydraulic, mobile, and fully automated inspection well systems along with their accompanying accessories.
Inspection of the equipment used for the production and processing of concrete modules for inspection wells Zhengzhou: Assembly site for the equipment used for manufacturing well wall brick modules
Inspection of equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for wells Characteristics and advantages of Zhengzhou equipment for well wall brick modules:
The Yixin inspection well block brick machine equipment is widely applicable to new types of masonry materials for municipal underground structures such as coal, heat, water, electricity, and gas facilities.
Examples include various inspection wells for drainage and water storage facilities, stormwater inlets, square ditches, septic tanks, small structures, and bridge wing walls.
The advantage of using concrete modules to construct inspection wells is that the modules have ridged and grooved structures on all their sides (upper, lower, left, and right), which when assembled together form a interlocking chain.
The shear resistance of the well wall is significantly better than that of the masonry constructed using plain frictional bonding methods.
The module has a hollow structure; when assembled and constructed, the longitudinal holes are interconnected, and the transverse holes also intersect with each other. After the cores of these holes are poured, a cast-in-place concrete mesh structure is formed, which provides additional reinforcement and waterproofing benefits.
The module is equipped with reinforcement slots both horizontally and vertically; the horizontal reinforcement bars and vertical reinforcement bars enhance the overall strength of the structure accordingly.
In addition, inspection wells and drainage wells constructed using concrete inspection well modules are less prone to collapse, subsidence, or leakage. The mechanical properties of the well wall modules are stable, the installation process is simple, and the formed dimensions meet standard requirements.
The intelligent control system for the concrete inspection well module brick manufacturing equipment is equipped with data input and output devices. A one-touch LCD display monitors the entire mechanical operation process, enabling ideal human-machine interaction, automatic material ratio analysis, density control, safety logic management, and a fault diagnosis system.
The mechanical-hydraulic systems for the well wall module construction utilize single-cylinder and double-cylinder hydraulic technologies for both transportation and other functions.
The independent hydraulic integration station eliminates the impact of vibrations from the main machine on the hydraulic system, ensuring the reliability of its operation.
The equipment for manufacturing concrete inspection well module bricks includes a material distribution box, a traveling mold box, and a mold removal mechanism. The mold box rises after the process is completed, and the door of the material storage box closes. The automatic conveying trays are also operated independently by the hydraulic system. This approach aims to reduce mechanical wear and the need for maintenance.
The concrete inspection well module brick manufacturing equipment uses imported computers and electrical components, as well as seals and hydraulic parts, ensuring the overall stability and reliability of the equipment.
The mechanical vibration platform for the well wall module is constructed using integral sheet steel. The tabletop is precision-cut using wire cutting technology, and the mold assembly is completed without any welding points, allowing the filler box to swing freely and guide its movement. This design significantly reduces mechanical wear and tear.
Reduce the mold load, combine the packing process with the vibration amplitude encryption in one system; adopt an integrated and fully synchronized approach that includes both table vibration and mold vibration to ensure optimal compaction results.
The well wall module is mechanically excited using specialized equipment, with the amplitude automatically controlled by a computer based on the cost-effectiveness of the raw materials. This system eliminates wear and tear on the braking components, thereby extending the module’s service life and reducing costs.
The well wall module features both mechanical automatic control and manual control functions.
Inspection of the well casing mold:
