The China Children’s Center will organize a series of activities to allow children to experience “high technology” on Children’s Day (June 1st) – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20th (Huang Xiaoxi, Zhou Shanshan) Reporters learned from the China Children’s Center on the 20th that from May 28th to June 1st, around Children’s Day, the center plans to organize a series of events including children’s maker experiences, a children’s visual arts festival, and a parent-child book carnival, allowing children to celebrate Children’s Day in the midst of the charm of cutting-edge technology.
It is understood that the activities organized by the China Children’s Center during this year’s Children’s Day on June 1st include the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival, the first Children’s Visual Arts Festival, the “Bookish Carnival,” and a series of activities related to picture books titled “The Whole Family Loves Reading.”
Li Zhongming, the deputy director of the China National Children’s Center, introduced at the media briefing for the 2016 Children’s Day on June 20th that the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival is the main event organized by the China National Children’s Center to celebrate Children’s Day this year.
The event focuses on the organic integration of social innovation with the creative ideas of individuals and families. By involving children and families in various innovative educational activities, it aims to make innovative practices a cultural aspect of ordinary households, and to turn “doing things with one’s own hands” into a new way of learning and living for many families.
It is reported that the “Aijia Chuangku” Children’s Future Learning Carnival includes a variety of cutting-edge technology experiences, such as the “Douguo Maker” experience program, the anniversary celebration of the Laoniu Children’s Exploration Museum and the “Explore Family Love, Have a Fun Children’s Day” event, the VR public experience program, and the “Maker Tribe” interactive workshop.
