Ingredients for the beauty and skin-nourishing soup:
The benefits of White Fungus (Tremella fuciformis): It has a sweet taste and a mild nature, and it corresponds to the lung, stomach, and kidney meridians. Its effects include strengthening the essence, nourishing the kidneys, moistening the intestines, benefiting the stomach, replenishing qi, harmonizing the blood, strengthening the heart, nourishing yin, moistening the lungs, promoting the production of body fluids, enhancing physical vitality, benefiting the brain, invigorating the mind, beautifying the skin, making the skin more tender, and prolonging life. It is used to treat
The effects of peach gum: It has a bitter taste and a neutral nature, and it belongs to the Large Intestine and Bladder meridians.
Benefits: It helps to regulate blood flow, promotes urination, stops diarrhea, relieves pain, and also provides hydration while moisturizing the intestines. For those who suffer from constipation, consuming more peach gum can be beneficial.
The effects of Goji berries: They have a neutral nature and a sweet taste, and they are associated with the liver and stomach meridians.
Benefits the liver and improves eyesight; nourishes the liver and kidneys; promotes skin whitening and beautification; enhances vitality and promotes the production of body fluids; slows down the aging process.
The benefits of red dates: They have a sweet taste and a mild nature, and they affect the spleen and stomach meridians. Red dates help to strengthen the spleen and stomach, replenish qi, generate body fluids, nourish the blood, and calm the mind. Those with a weak spleen and stomach, insufficient qi and blood, or who suffer from insomnia can benefit from consuming more red dates.
The benefits of longan pulp: It has a sweet taste and a warm nature, and it affects the heart and spleen meridians. It is suitable for those with deficiencies in both the heart and spleen.
Longan pulp can also moisturize the skin and enhance its beauty, nourish the blood and soothe the mind, benefit the heart and spleen, strengthen sexual function, and boost energy. It is suitable for people with anemia as well as those who suffer from insomnia.
The effects of lotus seeds: They have a sweet and astringent taste, and a neutral nature. They are associated with the heart, spleen, and kidney meridians.
It helps to soothe the mind and calm the nerves, alleviates symptoms such as palpitations and insomnia, addresses stomach weakness and forgetfulness, relieves irritability and thirst, provides nourishment to replenish deficiencies in the body, and stops excessive urination and sperm leakage.
Therefore, this beauty-enhancing soup is not only a delicious dessert but also beneficial for your health!
Eating more can help you feel mentally peaceful and well-balanced!
