Actually, there are many considerations regarding the clothing choices for girls who are slightly overweight.
Girls who are overweight should not wear skirts that are too short or too long; the length should be around the knees, just enough to cover the fattier parts of their thighs.
If a skirt is too short, it will highlight the fat on the legs.
If it’s too long, it can give the impression that someone is short and chubby.
If you wear clothes that are divided into three sections (top, middle, and bottom), it will make you look taller naturally. Simply using different colors for the top, skirt, and stockings can create an effect that makes your figure appear longer and slimmer.
In fact, many dark-colored clothes are a staple for girls who are slightly overweight (the author can attest to this), as dark colors are an excellent way to conceal a fuller figure. Elegant and sophisticated black skirts are also a top choice for such girls.
Wearing dark-colored clothes, especially a black skirt, can make you appear slimmer.
If your calves are quite thick, try not to wear socks and shoes that are too eye-catching.
The more popular it is, the better. Also, the colors shouldn’t be too bright.
To prevent people from noticing your legs and feet and thus giving the impression that you are overweight.
For slightly overweight girls, it’s really important to teach them the tricks of how to dress well and match their clothes properly.
Girls who are slightly overweight should definitely avoid wearing tight, short skirts. Also, the tops should not be too short or tucked into the skirt, as this can look very uncomfortable. If their legs are thicker, they should wear black stockings or mesh stockings (the type with a fine pattern). Choose a soft, printed flared skirt and pair it with a top with a loose neckline; this combination can effectively hide any potential shortcomings associated with being overweight.
Of course, even slightly plump girls have their own considerations when it comes to wearing short skirts.
A chubby girl wearing a short skirt should choose a top that matches the color of the skirt. This will create an illusion that makes her plump figure appear taller.
A short skirt paired with high heels can make your legs look longer and slimmer—this is definitely the most trendy combination for summer!
If you’re a girl with a larger upper body but thinner legs, I recommend choosing a gorgeous one-piece skirt that has a stylish and elegant look.
It not only covers your big belly, but also highlights your best features.
A-line skirts can really make you look slimmer and are more suitable for girls who are a bit plumper. For the top, choose something a bit tighter to create a layered look, which will also help you appear thinner.
A simple white T-shirt paired with a short skirt – even plump girls can try this out.
Even slightly plump girls can look stylish when they dress appropriately.
As long as they can master the rules of dressing and styling, even slightly plump girls can become the center of attention.
Now that I’ve made changes to my clothing style, I also need to exercise more in my daily life and strive to get rid of the label of being a “slightly overweight girl” as soon as possible 😄
The 18th “World Beverage Innovation Awards” are an award presented in collaboration by FoodBev Media and the German international beer, brewing, and beverage industry exhibition, Brau Beviale, which takes place in Nuremberg.
A total of 279 entries were received, representing 22 different categories from 25 countries.
On October 15th, the list of finalists for the competition was announced. The final list of winners will be published online on November 11th (British Summer Time).
We see that the LP28 sugar-free yogurt from Yuanqi Forest has been nominated for the Best Dairy Beverage Award; the “GOGO Wuhan” marketing campaign by Yili Amuji has been nominated for the Best Marketing Campaign Award; and the packaging collaboration between PepsiCo and People’s Daily New Media has also been nominated for the Best Packaging Design/Label Award.
Laura Nettle, Senior Marketing Director at FoodBev Media, said: “We are delighted to celebrate the 18th anniversary of the annual World Beverage Innovation Awards together with Brau Beviale.”
From new flavors, concepts, and features to branding, packaging, and manufacturing processes, we observe trends in the beverage industry as the sector continues to innovate in more sustainable ways.
The World Beverage Innovation Awards recognize the most ambitious new products and developments from both established and emerging brands in the global beverage industry this year.
Here is the complete list of finalists for each category in the finals:
The technology developed by the Ardagh Group enables 100% of recycled glass to be remelted into new bottles.
The water is packaged in bags inside boxes that are made from 100% recyclable materials. This reduces packaging waste by 66% and carbon emissions by 97%.
LatCub is 100% biodegradable, uses less paper, and does not contain any glues or tapes that are harmful to the environment.
The technology developed by the Ardagh Group enables 100% of recycled glass to be remelted and used to produce new bottles.
The final list of winners will be announced on November 11th (British Summer Time) on the FoodBev Media YouTube channel. FBIF will continue to keep you updated on all the developments, so stay tuned!
