Claimed to have the loudest exhaust sound among all the supercars in the New Mountain District!
The car that our team has brought for everyone this time is the dream of many men!
It is the flagship supercar from Lamborghini, the successor to the Murcielago – the Aventador LP700-4!
The price is nearly two million Malaysian ringgit, and the annual road tax is just over ten thousand Malaysian ringgit. It’s a four-wheel-drive vehicle – so why is it called the LP700?
With 700 horsepower, you can imagine just how fast it would be.
Well, I don’t really know either. The data shows that the acceleration from 0 to 100 km/h only takes 2.9 seconds. That means by the time my Myvi reaches 30 km/h, the other vehicle might already be going at 100 km/h. Hmm.
The low-profile car body, the aggressive scissor doors, the large air inlets surrounding the entire vehicle, and the 6.5-liter V12 engine clearly visible through the glass perfectly embody the Lamborghini style.
There’s not much need to say about the descriptions of the car models; just Google them if you want to know more. The editor has compiled some additional explanations that might not be available directly through Google searches!
It’s too much attention; wherever I go, everyone is looking at me, which is really uncomfortable! (Actually, it’s kind of cool in a way.)
The cost of fuel for a 1-kilometer journey is around RM1 (the car owner doesn’t really care about it at all).
You need to practice the proper way of getting in and out of the vehicle; otherwise, it can be a bit embarrassing (you might get stuck inside the cabin and unable to move).
The engine noise is so loud that you’ll go deaf as soon as you get out of the car. (But it’s still really exciting.)
The car is too large; if it were parked in a regular parking space, it would be very cramped. I’m really worried that the doors of the car next to it might hit it when they are opened!
It’s a bit lonely because there are no competitors on the road (that’s what the editor said; it has nothing to do with the car owners, haha).
