A few days prior to that, millions of Porsche 911s and tens of millions of supercars from the Chiron series were destroyed abroad in just a few minutes!
Looking at the results, it makes sense that the price is higher!
Let the spirit of the university resonate in harmony with the spirit of the times – Xinhua News Agency
The so-called "university spirit" refers to a series of educational philosophies and value pursuits that have been gradually established over the long term in the development of a university, representing the very essence of that institution.
From ancient times to the present, the spirit of universities has been of paramount importance for the development of politics, economics, culture, technology, society, and even the progress of a nation as a whole.
Since the birth of the world’s first modern university, universities have undertaken a unique mission that sets them apart from other social organizations. For the universities in our country, which emerged during times of national crisis, their spirit has been profoundly influenced by traditional culture and the changes of the times. They advocate for the values of “cultivating virtue to benefit society” and “improving oneself, regulating one’s family, governing the state, and bringing peace to the world,” as well as the patriotic commitment to “strengthening the nation through education.”
Currently, the trends of informatization and internationalization in higher education are becoming increasingly evident. The competition in education, technology, and talent on a global scale is intensifying. As a crucial “supply-side” component of the higher education system, its structural reforms are facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges.
In particular, the introduction of the "Comprehensive Plan for Promoting the Development of World-Class Universities and Disciplines" demonstrates our country's confidence and determination in transitioning from a major player in higher education to a powerhouse in this field. It also sets higher and more modern requirements for the development of universities.
How can we strive to become among the world’s best in a relatively short period of time, and on the basis of existing gaps, accelerate the establishment of several world-class universities and a number of world-class disciplines, thereby achieving a “catch-up” or “overtaking” on the curve?
In addition to having firm confidence in their goals, the path they choose, and their own capabilities, universities should also fully leverage three key advantages: 1. The advantage of being latecomers: By continuously attracting outstanding academic talents from abroad and learning from the advanced experiences of world-class universities, they can significantly improve their academic standards and the quality of education provided. 2. The cultural advantage: By inheriting the wisdom accumulated over five thousand years of Chinese civilization and promoting the development of excellent traditional culture, universities can build cohesion, shape a strong brand, and enhance their overall image. 3. The institutional advantage: As socialist countries
It is particularly important to realize that building world-class universities cannot mean that all universities should look the same. While each university should leverage its strengths, it must also showcase its unique personality and characteristics.
The distinctive features of a school should not only reflect the common Chinese characteristics but also embody each school's unique goals, educational traditions, and resource endowments.
In the case of Zhejiang University, we focus on highlighting three distinctive aspects in our educational approach: First, we emphasize the cultivation of innovative and entrepreneurial talents by creating an integrated educational environment that combines science and education, as well as collaboration between universities and enterprises, thereby forming a comprehensive ecosystem for entrepreneurship education. Second, we foster the convergence of different disciplines by promoting the optimization and adjustment of the academic curriculum, establishing an institutional framework that encourages interdisciplinary research, and actively supporting the development of new interdisciplinary fields and significant collaborative achievements. Third, we highlight the role of the university in serving society by engaging in extensive international exchanges and collaborations
In this process, it is particularly important to always uphold the university spirit and ensure that it resonates in harmony with the spirit of the times.
For Zhejiang University, the motto “Seeking Truth and Innovation,” the shared values of “Diligent Learning, Cultivating Virtue, Making Clear Discriminations, and Being Honest and Down-to-Earth,” as well as the mission of “Embracing All Rivers and Streams, Promoting Truth and Virtue, Leading the People Forward, and Building Our Nation,” collectively constitute the latest expression of the university’s spirit.
This is an important guarantee for the school to maintain the correct direction in its educational efforts, continuously build up a high level of cultural heritage, and unite spiritual strength. It is rich in meaning and has far-reaching significance.
Among these, “Haina Jianghe” (Embracing Rivers and Streams) emphasizes the spirit of openness and inclusiveness, reflecting the ambition to “utilize the talents from all over the world for our own benefit” by adopting high-quality educational concepts from renowned international institutions. “Qizhen Houde” (Promoting Truth and Virtue) highlights the pursuit of truth and goodness, suggesting that universities should not only seek knowledge but also cultivate virtue and strengthen their moral character. “Kaiwu Qianmin” (Innovating for the People) embodies the spirit of reform and advancement, encompassing both the pursuit of new
This series of spiritual concepts and value pursuits is precisely the essence of Zhejiang University’s 120-year history of education.
“The wise hear what is silent; the discerning perceive what has yet to take form.”
Chinese universities should further align themselves with the overall framework of the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics, deeply understand the historical context and mission of higher education in our era, and accelerate their efforts to become world-class institutions.
At the same time, it is essential to uphold humanistic care and independence, allowing the spirit of the university to interact with the spirit of the times and the national spirit. This interaction generates a continuous source of momentum for achieving national prosperity and rejuvenation, as well as for realizing the common ideals of humanity.
