Have you encountered any issues with the required hours of continuing education for the initial registration of Level 1 Cost Engineers?
Individuals who registered after the deadline did not provide proof of continuing education. For late registration, proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education within the past year is required. For re-registration, proof of at least 120 hours of continuing education within the past 4 years is necessary. Additionally, for each full year since the last registration, proof of at least 30 hours of continuing education must be provided.
Cost Engineering Professional Continuing Education Fee Standards
Cost engineers participating in online continuing education must pay the learning fees to the respective management institutions when registering. The general standard is as follows: The fee for 30 hours of compulsory courses is 300 yuan per person per year (including the unified continuing education textbooks).
The cost for a 30-hour elective course is 300 yuan per person per year.
The cost for 30 hours of compulsory courses and 30 hours of elective courses is 600 yuan per person per year (including the unified textbooks for continuing education).
(1) Participate in the online continuing education programs for registered cost engineers organized by the China Construction Cost Association or the provincial and departmental management agencies. The number of study hours is calculated based on the time recorded in the online learning materials.
(II) Participation in centralized face-to-face training for registered cost engineers organized by the China Construction Cost Association or provincial and departmental management agencies, as well as various types of training courses and seminars, can be recognized as 4 academic hours per half day.
(III) Participating in continuing education courses for cost engineers and cost estimators organized by the China Construction Cost Association, as well as at the provincial and departmental levels; 10 academic hours can be recognized for each half-day of attendance.
(IV) Participation in research projects conducted by the China Price Association or provincial authorities, the development of industry standards, and the compilation of teaching materials is recognized as 30 academic hours per year for each project.
(VI) Participation in the compilation of textbooks for the national Cost Engineer Practice Qualification Examination, as well as in the process of setting exam questions, reviewing answers, and grading papers. This activity can be recognized as 30 academic hours per year.
(VII) Papers and works related to the field of construction cost estimation that are personally authored and publicly published (as evidenced by an official publication number).
For published works, 12 academic hours are recognized for every 10,000 words.
For papers published in national-level journals, 8 academic hours are recognized for every 1,000 words; for papers published in provincial-level journals, 5 academic hours are recognized for every 1,000 words; and for papers published in municipal-level journals, 3 academic hours are recognized for every 1,000 words.
(9) Participation in public training programs organized by engineering cost consulting enterprises that have been approved or authorized by the China National Price Association, provincial-level management agencies, and provincial cost associations is permitted (except for general corporate management and skills training). Four class hours can be recognized for each half-day of participation, with a maximum of 30 class hours recognized per year.
Cost Engineer Online Continuing Education Learning Process
Once the registration fee is received by the registration authority, the student’s account is activated immediately. The cost engineer can then log in to the online education platform using their username and password to begin their studies.
Students learn by accessing on-demand course materials, asking questions for answers, and participating in online discussions.
If you forget your password and encounter an error stating that either the username or password is incorrect when trying to log in, preventing you from accessing the learning materials, please contact the registration institution you are affiliated with. The registration institution can assist you in changing your password (but not your username). Once you have received the new password, you can log in again using it.
