That was the first time in my life that I wore makeup properly. Wow… I can’t believe I’ll ever look that good one day, haha.
Xiaojie and another girl (I’m sorry, I can’t remember her name) were extremely patient when applying makeup, and the results looked very natural.
The outdoor shots were taken in Jiangwan City. Fortunately, the weather was very good that day, so we didn’t feel too cold. During the shooting, the makeup artist kept an eye on our clothes and headgear; whenever something looked a bit out of place, she immediately helped us fix it.
The photographer was also very humorous, and we all had a great time taking pictures throughout the day.
When selecting the photos, since we had seen many examples online, we didn’t want the clients to have to delete too many photos. However, during the process of choosing the photos, not once was there any suggestion from them that we should add more photos; we stuck strictly to the 24 photos included in the package. (I heard from my cousin who got her wedding photos around the same time that she added over ten thousand extra photos to her package, which cost more than seven thousand yuan. I was really amazed by that, and I was also quite worried that I might choose too many photos myself.)
The photos were fixed today, and Lannan sent them to me. After looking at two of them, I thought they weren’t quite good, so they immediately helped me fix them again.
I dug out some old photos my sister took and compared them. I’m really satisfied with the way our photos turned out; they’re simple, fresh, and exactly the style I was looking for.
I highly recommend everyone to go to Xuanhan Jin Furen to take their wedding photos!
