Your name is Zheng Mian, and this is your second week since you moved to Japan.
You’re walking down the street when you suddenly realize that someone is following you. Frightened, you start walking faster and faster, and eventually you begin to run.
That person was chasing after you from behind, saying, “Miss! Please wait!” (The entire conversation is in Japanese.) You stopped at the entrance of the convenience store.
“Miss… I’m a director, and I think you’re very beautiful. Would you be interested in participating in a reality show?”
You’re very skeptical and afraid that this might be a scam.
He handed you a business card, and you found out that he is indeed the director of a large Japanese entertainment company.
“If the miss has time, we could go to the company to discuss it. The payment for her role will definitely not be less than what’s been offered.”
You just kind of followed him to the company without really knowing what you were doing. He said he saw you on the street at first sight and really hoped you would come and join them.
You thought there would be no loss and you could even make money, so you signed the contract.
