President of the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina: Firmly believe that China has the capacity to organize the Winter Olympics successfully during this special period – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Sarajevo, December 11th – The President of the Bosnian Olympic Committee, Kvesić, recently stated that Bosnia is very much looking forward to the Beijing Winter Olympics and firmly believes that China has the capability to organize a successful Olympic event during this special period.
Recently, Ji Ping, the Chinese Ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina, met with Kvetic, the President of the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina, at the Sarajevo Olympic Center.
During the meeting, Kvesić spoke positively about the relations between Bosnia and China. He mentioned that he had visited China during the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics and was deeply impressed by the excellent organizational work displayed by the Chinese side. He expressed his firm belief that China has the capability to host a successful Winter Olympics under special circumstances. Bosnia is looking forward to the Beijing Winter Olympics with great anticipation, and the Bosnian Olympic Committee is actively preparing for participation in the event. Kvesić also expressed the hope that this opportunity would lead to broader exchanges and cooperation with China in the field of sports.
Ji Ping stated that China and Poland have a special “Olympic bond.”
The 1984 Winter Olympics in Sarajevo were successfully held here, and in two months, the 2022 Winter Olympics in Beijing will also kick off, presenting the world with a simple, safe, and spectacular event.
We look forward to further enhancing exchanges and cooperation between the two countries in areas such as the preparation for winter sports events and the training of athletes. The Chinese Embassy in Bosnia and Herzegovina is willing to continue playing a bridging role. Taking the Beijing Winter Olympics as an opportunity, we aim to promote the deepening of cultural exchanges between the two nations, enabling their peoples to “move together towards the future.” We also wish the Bosnian athletes great success in Beijing.
Before the meeting, the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina held the ceremony for the “10th Annual Best Athlete Award.” Ji Ping, as a special guest, presented the award to the best young athlete in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Promotional videos for the Beijing Winter Olympics were played in a loop at the event site.
