Negative nucleic acid test results within 48 hours, and the establishment of “buffer zones.” The Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council has issued a document calling for enhanced epidemic prevention and control measures in port cities – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 11 (Reporters Dong Ruifeng, Gu Tiancheng) The Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council recently issued a notice on strengthening the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pandemic in port cities. It requires that individuals who leave land border port cities (except those connected to Hong Kong and Macau by ports) must hold a negative nucleic acid test result within 48 hours, and those traveling to such cities must undergo at least one nucleic acid test upon arrival.
According to the notification, the time frame for the aforementioned requirements is from the date when each province, autonomous region, and municipality determines the list of port cities and announces it, until March 15, 2022.
In addition, the notification suggests that port cities with the appropriate conditions may consider establishing buffer zones for epidemic prevention and control within their jurisdictions.
A responsible official from the Disease Prevention and Control Bureau of the National Health Commission explained that for some port cities, cross-border trade is a major economic pillar, and there is frequent exchange of people between the border communities on both sides.
By implementing a differentiated management policy based on zoning, the approach has been shifted from having just one line of defense against the spread of the outbreak to having two lines of defense. This change is expected to move the focus of prevention and control further forward, thereby reducing the risk of the outbreak spreading. The goal is to achieve the greatest effectiveness in epidemic prevention and control with the least possible social impact and at the lowest social cost.
Recently, several local clustered outbreaks have occurred in our country, all of which were imported from overseas epidemics through port cities.
The aforementioned notice indicates that these issues have been exposed, such as the lack of timely monitoring and early warning of the epidemic in some areas, the failure to implement closed-loop management for personnel in high-risk positions, the perfunctory nature of regular nucleic acid testing, inadequate disinfection at all stages of the cold chain, non-standard management of centralized isolation facilities, and the insufficiently scientific and precise emergency response to the epidemic.
The notification requires efforts to be made in nine areas, including improving the epidemic prevention and control mechanisms in port cities, enhancing the epidemic monitoring and early warning systems, and implementing border control measures. These efforts aim to quickly address the shortcomings and weaknesses in the prevention and control capabilities of port cities. It is essential to maintain a rigorous and scientific approach to prevention and control work, and to strengthen the defenses against the introduction of infections from outside.
The notification emphasizes that cities with ports should conduct simultaneous research and planning for both epidemic prevention and control measures and the protection of people’s livelihoods. They should make the hotlines for livelihood support available to the public, regularly check for potential issues related to the supply of basic necessities and prices, and promptly address and respond to the prominent concerns raised by the public.
According to the notification, the port cities referred to include the counties (cities, districts, banners) where the open land, water, and air ports are located, as well as the cities (prefectures, leagues) and directly-administered municipalities where these ports are situated. The specific scope will be determined by each province (autonomous region, directly-administered municipality) based on the needs of epidemic prevention and control, and will be announced in a timely manner.
