I came across the following article by chance, which discusses from both a commercial and a storage perspective why this client prefers to use a logistics company located in a bonded area for the canning process. Although canning is considered a form of advanced processing and falls outside the scope of services provided by bonded logistics companies, the text may help explain why the client has made this choice.
I visited many manufacturers of milk powder and got in touch with their production lines.
In fact, the raw materials used for both bagged and canned powdered milk are exactly the same; there is no difference between them at all.
So, everyone must be wondering: Why is the shelf life of the bagged product one year, while that of the canned product two years or even longer?
Or another question: Why is there such a big price difference between canned and bagged products?
In fact, from this perspective, many consumers, or those in the motherhood group, believe that the quality is much better because the raw materials used are different.
Actually, the raw materials are the same; it’s just that people think the more expensive ones are the better.
Some consumers, with this mindset, have reported that the texture or taste of the canned products is indeed different after consumption.
Now, let me first explain to you the reasons why canned food is expensive. What exactly makes it costly?
If their raw materials are the same, why is there such a big difference in price?
Because when manufacturers set prices, they usually take into account the fact that if the price for bagged products is too high, consumers will find it difficult to accept. This means that the profits generated by the manufacturers would be very low, or even non-existent. So, how can manufacturers survive in such a situation?
Therefore, they have implemented a significant increase in the pricing of their canned products in order to ensure their profit margin.
Therefore, most manufacturers primarily promote canned products, rather than those packaged in bags.
Moreover, the manufacturers for whom you have such high expectations spend tens of millions, or even hundreds of millions, on annual advertising expenses. Where does all this money come from?
As you can all imagine…
As society develops, the costs associated with market promotion also continue to rise. These include expenses for promotional staff in shopping malls, display costs for products, costs of giving away free items with products, and advertising expenses, among others.
Therefore, various manufacturers are constantly introducing new products, and these products come in canned or bottled form. The prices of these products are also continuously rising. In fact, this is due to the increase in market costs.
The main objective is to achieve higher profits; in fact, the increased cost of their raw materials will not exceed 3 or 4 yuan at most.
There are also some brands that, in order to promote their products, will stop at nothing and establish connections with doctors in hospitals, asking them to assist with the promotion of those products. In return, these brands offer profits ranging from 30 to 80 yuan per product sold.
The relevant laws in China absolutely do not permit such practices; in fact, this behavior is considered to be harming consumers.
It is recommended that everyone buy powdered milk in pouch form and transfer it into jars at home, provided they already have jars available. This can help save money and improve the shelf life and sealing of the powdered milk. Moreover, it will not have any negative impact on the children.
Also, please don’t assume that the shelf life of canned products is longer than that of bagged products. If the shelf life is the same for both after opening, it’s just that bagged products are more difficult to store and are prone to becoming damp and deteriorating.
