The reserves of the naked carp in Qinghai Lake have increased by 0.71 million tons this year – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (Reporters Luo Xiaofei, Zhang Hongxiang) Reporters learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserves of the naked carp in Qinghai Lake have increased by 7,100 tons this year compared to last year, reaching 108,500 tons. This represents a cumulative increase of more than 40 times since the initial protection measures were implemented in 2002.
The Qinghai Lake naked carp, commonly known as the “Huang fish,” is a unique and precious species found only in Qinghai Lake. It plays a vital role in maintaining the security of the “water-fish-bird” ecological chain and biodiversity within the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to factors such as extensive human hunting and the deteriorating environmental conditions in the areas where the Qaidam fish (Gymnocyprinus przewalskii) reproduced, the population of this species declined sharply. By 2002, the reserves of Qaidam fish in Qinghai Lake had dwindled to just 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the “China Species Red List”.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented a policy of closing lakes to promote fish conservation. No entity, group, or individual is allowed to fish for the naked carp in Qinghai Lake and its main rivers and tributaries, and the sale of naked carp and its products is prohibited.
Meanwhile, efforts to protect the resources of the Qinghai Lake naked carp have been continuously intensified through measures such as artificial propagation and reintroduction into the lake, cleaning the river channels that flow into Qinghai Lake, and designing scientifically sound and reasonable “fish passages.” As a result, the population of these fish has been increasing year by year.
Yang Lin, the deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, introduced that as of now, nearly 180 million individuals of the Qinghai Lake naked carp have been artificially propagated and released into the lake. The contribution of this initiative to the recovery of the Qinghai Lake naked carp population exceeds 23%.
The Sanjiangyuan area in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation region for not only China but also for Asia. Lake Qinghai serves as a natural barrier that prevents the desertification in the west from spreading eastward, as well as fulfilling important ecological functions.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Sanjiangyuan area and the Qinghai Lake basin, as well as the aquatic wildlife, and to maintain the biodiversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has issued bans on fishing in key waters of the Yangtze River, the Yellow River, and Qinghai Lake since the beginning of this year. As a result, a comprehensive fishing ban management system has been established for each river and lake.
