The chips with glass substrates are tested with pure water at an injection pressure of 800 mbar (for 100 μm channels) before shipment. Please be careful not to collide the chips with sharp objects during use, as this may damage the substrate.
During use, please take into account the viscosity of the solution and do not exceed the specified range; otherwise, leakage may occur.
For microfluidic microchips with a common substrate, when using a syringe pump for sample injection with pure water, we recommend setting the flow rate below 150 ul/min. For the oil phase, we suggest setting the flow rate below 50 ul/min.
Consider the actual viscosity of the liquid being injected, and gradually increase the value of your flow rate parameter from low to high.
After completing the experiments with the general-purpose chip, make sure to clean the internal channels promptly; otherwise, they may become clogged easily.
Microfluidic chips are considered consumables and cannot be reused repeatedly for an extended period of time.
No refunds or exchanges will be provided if the chip is damaged due to long-term use or improper handling.
