Yunnan: Coordinating and standardizing the management of public welfare positions in rural areas – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Kunming, December 12 (Reporter Lin Bifeng) In order to continue providing employment assistance to people who have been lifted out of poverty and to consolidate and expand the achievements of poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province has recently introduced relevant policies regarding the management of public welfare positions in rural areas, with the aim of promoting the comprehensive revitalization of the countryside.
A relevant official from the Yunnan Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security stated that to date, Yunnan has created a total of 448,300 public welfare jobs in rural areas, aimed at providing employment for people who have been lifted out of poverty and other disadvantaged rural groups. These jobs play a crucial role in helping impoverished individuals achieve employment and income growth, consolidating the achievements of poverty alleviation efforts, and effectively enhancing the provision of various public services in rural communities.
These new regulations were jointly issued by seven departments in Yunnan, including the Human Resources and Social Security Department, the Rural Revitalization Department, and the Finance Department. They mainly aim to standardize aspects such as the scope of candidates for recruitment to rural public welfare positions at the grassroots level, fund management, position development, and position management.
In terms of job development and staffing arrangements, the new regulations specify that the setup should be carried out in accordance with the principles of “establishing positions based on needs, assigning personnel to positions, managing dynamically, and controlling the total number of positions”; “the person who develops the position is responsible for using it and managing it”; as well as “one person per position, voluntary participation, and unified management.”
The recruitment process must be carried out in accordance with the following steps: announcement, application submission, review, public disclosure, employment, pre-job training, and assignment to a position.
In addition, the new regulations clarify the specific responsibilities of the departments responsible for developing rural public welfare jobs, as well as the subsidy standards and methods for these jobs. They stipulate that each department responsible for developing rural public welfare jobs must purchase commercial insurance for accidental injuries for the employees assigned to these positions. The relevant departments are also required to regularly supervise the distribution of subsidies for rural public welfare jobs.
