Let’s take a look at some of the [strange trending searches] today.
What is considered a normal public opinion?
Randomly select three trending searches: “The Dragon Rises on the Second Day of the Second Lunar Month,” “Good Luck Friends (a brand) increasing prices,” and “The Huolala incident.” Public opinion spreads, forming peaks, followed by a “decrease in the index” (represented by a smooth curve), and eventually the trend dissipates. If secondary public opinion emerges, a small peak may reappear.
They look exactly the same as the [Online Public Opinion Evolution Model] that was previously displayed on the official website of the Cyberspace Administration of China.
What is abnormal public opinion?
Randomly select six trending searches from the same event, and present them in the forms of “isolated peak,” “zigzag,” and “cliff.”
**Island Peak Pattern:** This refers to a situation where content is artificially heated (made more popular) and quickly climbs the search rankings, attracting widespread attention from the public. **Sawtooth Pattern:** This involves periodic increases in popularity, ensuring that the topic remains on the search rankings for an extended period. **Cliff Edge Pattern:** This occurs when all interest in the topic fades suddenly; once the search trend has fulfilled its purpose, it is replaced by new content and moves on to another “battlefield” (i.e., another topic becomes the focus of public attention).
In Figure 9, the peak of one event’s popularity coincides precisely with the trough of another event, down to the very second. This must indicate that a group of coordinated “water army” (internet trolls or botnet users) was given a task to launch a new round of attacks.
The专业化 of black public relations is evident in this case: dozens of trending topics make it onto the list simultaneously. These topics are carefully selected to either attract attention, disseminate scientific knowledge, stir up controversy, divert attention, influence perception, mislead judgment, arouse emotions, or influence decision-making. The accounts belonging to these black propaganda networks operate in a meticulous manner, dividing their efforts into batches and at specific moments, taking into account almost all the factors involved in the spread of public opinion.
Communication is a science. By setting aside all subjective factors such as opinions and emotions, and focusing solely on objective data, even black PR (negative public relations efforts) will have no place to hide.
Everything that passes leaves a trace, and we dig those traces out together.
Data source: The “Hot Searches Time Machine”.
Countries such as Mauritius have reported their first cases of infection with the Omicron variant – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 12 – According to reports from Xinhua’s correspondents abroad, Mauritius, Cyprus, and Malawi have recently reported their first cases of infection with the Omicron variant of the COVID-19 virus.
Mauritius reported its first two cases of the Omicron variant on the 10th.
According to Minister of Health Kailesh Jagutpal, one of the infected individuals was a tourist who departed from South Africa and arrived in Mauritius on November 27; the other infected person was a local resident of Mauritius who tested positive for the virus on November 30 after coming into contact with someone who had recently visited South Africa and then returned to Mauritius.
After being isolated and treated in the hospital, the nucleic acid test results for both of these infected individuals turned negative. They have now returned to their respective residences.
On the 10th, the Cyprus Ministry of Health announced that the country had detected its first three cases of infection with the Omicron variant.
All three of these people are students who returned from abroad at the beginning of this month. Since their symptoms were mild, they did not need to be hospitalized for treatment.
To prevent the spread of the Omicron variant, the Serbian government is continuously intensifying its prevention and control measures.
From December 6th to January 10th of next year, all passengers over the age of 12 entering the country by air will be required to pay for a nucleic acid test at the airport upon arrival.
On the 10th, the Serbian Ministry of Health also announced that it would begin vaccinating children aged 5 to 11 in the country with the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine.
On the 9th, Kunbize Chiponda, the Minister of Health of Malawi, announced that the country had detected its first three cases of infection with the Omicron variant.
The country's health department conducted genomic sequencing on 12 COVID-19 positive samples collected between November 9 and December 2, and identified these three cases of infection.
