The Great Beauty 360 integrates with home decoration solutions.
Address: 156 Huancheng South Road, Happiness Home, 12th Floor
It all started with a friend’s recommendation; out of trust, I decided to give it a try. My initial budget was 70,000 yuan for basic renovations.
As soon as they arrived at the store, a series of deceptive tactics were initiated.
This was my first time visiting the store. I just showed them my floor plan, and they didn’t even measure the house on-site. Yet, they were able to give me a quote, stating that they could sell my 135-square-meter house for 70,000 yuan. They briefly showed me some of the materials they would use, but I had no idea what brand those materials were.
Their second trick is that as soon as you arrive at the store, they will try to persuade you to pay the deposit. Once you pay that money, you will never be able to get it back, unless you have enough experience to argue and negotiate with them.
While I was hesitating about whether to pay the deposit, they would invite their so-called manager to explain to you how much discount you could get if you paid the deposit today.
This is a big scam; I’m a living example of someone who was deceived. In a moment of impulse, I paid a deposit of over ten thousand dollars.
The quote he gave me has many problems: The amount of 70,000 does not include the costs for renovating the plumbing and electricity systems, nor does it include any doors, cabinets, or the bathroom. Yet these three aspects are the main components that make up the bulk of the basic installation costs.
Apart from these issues, the fees they charge for their service points are also higher than those of other companies.
I have lost trust in this company; they didn’t explain anything clearly to me before asking me to sign the contract.
When I went to ask them for a refund, they seemed very experienced; there was even a dedicated team specifically designed to deal with such situations.
In any case, it would be argued that it was the customer’s problem, and they bear no responsibility at all.
There are all sorts of excuses for shirking responsibility, as well as many other details… I don’t want to go into them one by one; it would just make me cry. In short, don’t choose them. My friend also hired them to renovate her house, and the quality of the work was poor; they later tried to charge her for various additional expenses.
What a scam! Those things were originally just fake, deceptive decorative elements. Now they’ve been “rebranded” as something supposedly beautiful, but it seems the company went bankrupt again, and then they changed them into something else entirely.
So everyone, please don’t choose such a unreliable and dishonest renovation company.
In the future, when making choices, everyone should do more research by using Baidu to look up relevant information and seek advice. After all, home renovation is not a small investment.
