The joint medical exercise “Peace Rescue-2021” between the Chinese and Vietnamese armed forces has been successfully concluded – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Hanoi, December 12 (Zhou Na, Teng Huaijin) On the morning of December 12, all the Chinese units participating in the Sino-Vietnamese military joint exercise “Peace Rescue-2021” returned safely to Guangxi, China, marking the successful completion of the seven-day exercise.
During this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese armed forces focused on the important topic of humanitarian medical rescue, closely adhering to the mission of providing medical care and saving lives. They completed various tasks such as joint medical command, on-site rescue operations, and the treatment of large numbers of wounded personnel in accordance with practical combat standards, effectively enhancing the medical support capabilities of both armies.
The results of the exercise were recognized by the military forces of both China and Vietnam.
阮 Xiongsheng, the director of the Vietnamese Exercise Guidance Committee, deputy director of the General Logistics Department of the Vietnamese People’s Army, and chief of staff, stated at the ceremony marking the end of the exercise that through this training, Vietnamese military medical personnel learned about exercise organization and professional activities from their Chinese counterparts. They also got to see the medical and support equipment used by the Chinese side.
The results achieved through the exercise demonstrated the professional capabilities of the military medical forces from both countries in terms of medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control.
Chen Chunming, the head of the Chinese guidance and coordination group and the deputy director of the Health Bureau of the Logistics Support Department of the Central Military Commission, stated that this exercise represents another innovative and pioneering effort, built upon the successful joint medical consultation activities held in 2018. It holds great significance as a milestone in this area.
During the exercise, the Chinese People’s Liberation Army donated medical protective masks, protective clothing for medical use, and rapid nucleic acid testing equipment to the Vietnamese People’s Army, among other health and epidemic prevention supplies.
